quote: "The first altars I saw were in the woods,"
subject: Victorian Nature Poetry (1837–1901)
permalink: /Victorian Nature Poetry (1837–1901)/Robert Browning/Robert Browning - The Wood
---

The first altars I saw were in the woods,
When I was a child wandering far from home...
Nature's own mysteries embraced my heart,
And I breathed free; the flowers are my companions.
For, wherever they spring up, there shall I toil,
Neither am I unknown among the tides.

- Robert Browning
